CmdStanR: Fitting logistic growth - OBS model

Author

Benjamin Rosenbaum

Data preparation

rm(list=ls())
library("cmdstanr")

Rest of data preparation is identical to the rstan code.

data.in = read.csv("data_example_logistic.csv", row.names=1)

            m = m,

Stan model

Stan code is identical to the rstan case. Here it is coded as a string, and written to a .stan file.

write_stan_file(
  dir = getwd(),
  basename = "logistic_obs.stan",
  code = "
functions{
  vector odemodel(real t, vector N, vector p){
    // p[1]=r, p[2]=K
    vector[1] dNdt;
    dNdt[1] = p[1]*(1-(N[1]/p[2]))*N[1];
    return dNdt;
  }
}

data{
  int n; // observations
  int m; // replicates
  array[n] real t; 
  array[m,n] int N;
  real f;
}

parameters{
  real<lower=0> r;
  real<lower=0> K;
  real<lower=0> tau;
  vector<lower=0>[m] N0sim; // individual initial values for replicates
}

model{
  vector[2] p;
  array[n-1] vector[1] Nsim; // simulated values, matrix. dim1 = time without t0, dim2 = dim_ODE = 1
  
  // priors 
  r ~ lognormal(-2,1);
  K ~ lognormal(9,1);
  N0sim ~ normal(0,100);
  tau ~ gamma(2,0.1);
  
  // parameters for integrator
  p[1] = r;
  p[2] = K;
  
  for (j in 1:m){
    // integrate ODE
    Nsim = ode_rk45(odemodel, [N0sim[j]]', t[1], t[2:n], p);
    // likelihood
    N[j,1] ~ neg_binomial_2(N0sim[j]*f, tau);
    for (i in 2:n){
      N[j,i] ~ neg_binomial_2(Nsim[i-1,1]*f, tau);
    }  
  }
}

generated quantities{
  real alpha = r/K;
}
"
)

Model fitting

Initial values are coded as usual, as a list of lists, one per chain each.

chains = 3
# initial values for sampling 
init=rep(list(list(r=0.1,
                   K=1e4,
                   N0sim=data$N[, 1]/data$f,
                   tau=10))
         ,chains)

The model is compiled and sampling is started, with cmdstanr functions.

stanmodel = cmdstan_model("logistic_obs.stan")

fit = stanmodel$sample(
  data = data,    
  chains = chains,        
  parallel_chains = chains,              
  iter_warmup = 2000,          
  iter_sampling = 2000,            
  init = init
)
